-- Former Sonova CEO Tells TV Program Profit Warning Wasn’t Evident
-- B y   A l l i s o n   C o n n o l l y
-- 2012-04-16T08:05:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-16/former-sonova-ceo-tells-tv-program-profit-warning-wasn-t-evident.html
Former  Sonova Holding AG (SOON)  Chief
Executive Officer Valentin Chapero told Swiss television station
SF’s  ECO program  he sold shares last year without expecting the
hearing-aid maker would issue a profit warning a week later.  Although sales figures had been submitted to management
before the sale, the costs hadn’t been, Chapero said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Allison Connolly in Frankfurt at 
 aconnolly4@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Phil Serafino at   pserafino@bloomberg.net . 